<p>Almost all ideas can be explained in simple language, and maybe thereâ€™s no need for the â€œalmost.â€ The most complicated mathematics is built up from simple ideas. Complex language is usually a sort of shorthand used by experts when talking amongst themselves. This is true in many fields, not just philosophy.</p>

