<ul>
  <li>At each point, while weâ€™re expressing ourselves, our brains cook up multiple ways to say the same thing. In the end, we choose one. Most of the time, we only utter one, but sometimes these competing expressions bubble up into speech, creating redundancies. Theyâ€™re fascinating if you pay attention to them, because they show the composing mind at work.</li>
</ul>

<blockquote>
  <p>â€œPlease donâ€™t feel obliâ€¦ donâ€™t bother bringing anything to the party. I mean, you donâ€™t have to bring anything. It will just be nice â€¦ it will be great to see you, to spend time with you.â€</p>
