<ul>
  <li>
    <p>We sometimes worry that our words are confusing or obscure, and so we pack redundancies into our sentences to make sure listeners understand what weâ€™re talking about.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>â€œYouâ€™re going to have to use the longish key, you know, that one, to get in. Donâ€™t use any of the other keys, because they wonâ€™t work. You have to use that oneâ€¦ the long one.â€</p>
  </li>
